ttp://gu.com/p/4ehnk","liveBloggingNow":"false","body":"<p>When people come across Alice in Wonderland they tend to think it’s about fantasy and fairies and a book for babies. However, if they actually, bit by bit, turn the pages they will experience the bravery of Alice, the amusement of the Mad Hatter and the hatred of the Red Queen; they will find that this book is for anyone big or small, tall or short.<br /></p> <p>My favourite character was… Yes, after this you will hate me!… The Red Queen! I just loved the fact that she was hilarious as well as bossy and unfair (a bit like my mum!). Overall, I rate this book 9/10. Amazing. Loved it. I’m not a BIG fan of adventure stories but I loved this book. For anyone aged 0-100. </p>  <figure class=\"element element-image element--thumbnail\" data-media-id=\"fe836980e3537d9894fbc12162d3a42cad0ff989\"> <img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2015/11/26/1448553327047/7d1b4973-4f52-44a0-a501-783e79ea98f4-bestSizeAvailable.jpeg\" alt=\"Alice In Wonderland by Lewis Carroll\" width=\"260\" height=\"259\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"></span> </figcaption> </figure>  <ul> <li><strong>Buy this book at the <a href=\"https://bookshop.theguardian.com/alice-in-wonderland-24.html\">Guardian Bookshop</a></strong></li> </ul> <h2><strong>Want to tell the world about a book you’ve read?<a href=\"http://preview.gutools.co.uk/books/childrens-books/2011/mar/02/how-do-i-get-involved-guardian-childrens-books\">Join the site</a> and send us your review!</strong></h2>","productionOffice":"UK","hasStoryPackage":"false","trailText":"<strong>Mangomix: </strong>‘This book is for anyone big or small, tall or short… I loved it’","headline":"Alice In Wonderland by Lewis Carroll - review","byline":"Mangomix","commentable":"false","standfirst":"<p>‘This book is for anyone big or small, tall or short… I loved it’</p>"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/childrens-books-site/2015/de