 always going to be difficult, changing identity and having to lie to everyone you meet. But it seems to be going alright except when it comes to Chet Falconer, the only person who she really struggles to pretend around. Despite Stella’s best efforts, danger is fast approaching. Will she have the strength to do the right thing? Even if it means losing the life she once had?</p> <p>Becca Fitzpatrick has been an author I’ve looked up to for a while now, ever since I picked up a copy of her amazing Hush, Hush series. To most this might make me seem a bit biased but honestly it made me a harsher critic. Normally after an author creates a masterpiece of a series, the rest of their work in my eyes doesn’t live up to the expectations I’ve built for them. Especially after the roller coaster of feels you catch from a series where you can connect with a character and their journey. This is certainly not the case with Dangerous Lies. The realistic characters, fast-paced action and a complex storyline that unravels as you read along, you won’t be able to put it down.</p>  <figure class=\"element element-image element--thumbnail\" data-media-id=\"d3a82756d5c3ce43d771b87a888684bc193118f8\"> <img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2015/11/26/1448548046145/bf006b87-fbfb-4ba2-a5d3-ed63c2fd2470-273x420.jpeg\" alt=\"Dangerous Lies by Becca Fitzpatrick\" width=\"273\" height=\"420\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"></span> </figcaption> </figure>  <ul> <li><strong>Buy this book at the <a href=\"https://bookshop.theguardian.com/catalog/product/view/id/350244/\">Guardian Bookshop</a></strong></li> </ul> <h2><strong>Want to tell the world about a book you’ve read?<a href=\"http://preview.gutools.co.uk/books/childrens-books/2011/mar/02/how-do-i-get-involved-guardian-childrens-books\">Join the site</a> and send us your review!</strong></h2>","productionOffice":"UK","hasStoryPackage":"false","trailText":"<strong>Roseleen H